  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: 1.4.5-stable-a269a713\nOS & Version: Debian\nCommit hash : master\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nLog output to the provided file\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nThe `js` command consumes all following output including my `2>> /path/to/file` and geth throws an error.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\n`geth js randomFile.js 2 >> /dev/null`\n#### Backtrace\n\n```\ngeth js randomFile.js 2 >> /dev/null                                                 1 ↵\nI0601 22:37:08.089129 ethdb/database.go:82] Alloted 128MB cache and 1024 file handles to /home/firescar96/.ethereum/chaindata\nI0601 22:37:08.165794 ethdb/database.go:169] closed db:/home/firescar96/.ethereum/chaindata\nI0601 22:37:08.166195 ethdb/database.go:82] Alloted 128MB cache and 1024 file handles to /home/firescar96/.ethereum/chaindata\nI0601 22:37:08.235254 ethdb/database.go:82] Alloted 16MB cache and 16 file handles to /home/firescar96/.ethereum/dapp\nI0601 22:37:08.238660 eth/backend.go:172] Protocol Versions: [63 62 61], Network Id: 1\nI0601 22:37:08.238819 eth/backend.go:201] Blockchain DB Version: 3\nI0601 22:37:08.240278 core/blockchain.go:206] Last header: #1199583 [3576934b…] TD=10344961585528197150\nI0601 22:37:08.240310 core/blockchain.go:207] Last block: #1199583 [3576934b…] TD=10344961585528197150\nI0601 22:37:08.240323 core/blockchain.go:208] Fast block: #1199583 [3576934b…] TD=10344961585528197150\nI0601 22:37:08.241728 p2p/server.go:311] Starting Server\nI0601 22:37:10.201443 p2p/discover/udp.go:217] Listening, enode://4cac3b3c8b6ae089150d6ca5e968e5fb7175d47556f70f2e19d49417e4273bba666227d35d28feca962694cee0ad02585f6a3326386ab5fa1b622ace4ed822a6@[::]:30303\nI0601 22:37:10.201755 p2p/server.go:554] Listening on [::]:30303\nI0601 22:37:10.202169 node/node.go:298] IPC endpoint opened: /home/firescar96/.ethereum/geth.ipc\nFatal: JavaScript Error: open randomFile.js: no such file or directory\n```\n\nI believe this could be solved easily by reinstating the `--logfile` flag.\n",
