    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The number is part of shell syntax and redirects the 'standard error' stream (file descriptor no. 2).\nAll geth log output goes to stderr. We have chosen this setup because it is easier to handle when you want to run geth as a daemon through systemd or supervisord. Another reason why stderr is preferable is  that Go runtime exceptions are printed to stderr as well. We cannot write those to a file even if we wanted to so the best solution for us is to write all output to stderr.\n",
