    "body": "Here is my use case, I'm using meteor for a visualization and need to start a geth instance on the server upon user request. I need the log output sent to a file and it's helpful for debugging to simultaneously send output to the console. \n\nI've been using my fork so far because it's easy to do there:\n\n``` javascript\nlet cmd = spawn('geth', ['--datadir=' + gethInstanceConfig.datadir, '--dev',\n    '--logfile=' + gethInstanceConfig.logfile, '--port=' + gethInstanceConfig.port,\n    '--rpc', '--rpcport=' + gethInstanceConfig.rpcport, \n    '--rpcaddr=' + gethInstanceConfig.rpcaddr, '--rpcapi=' + \n    gethInstanceConfig.rpcapi, '--networkid=' + gethInstanceConfig.networkid,\n    '--rpccorsdomain=' + gethInstanceConfig.rpccorsdomain, '--unlock=0',\n    '--password=' + gethInstanceConfig.password,\n    '--bootnodes=' + gethInstanceConfig.bootnodes,\n    '--maxpeers=' + gethInstanceConfig.maxpeers, 'js', gethInstanceConfig.js]);\n```\n\nI can still get both stdout and stderr using this method:\n\n``` javascript\ncmd.stdout.on('data', (data) => {\n  console.log(data.toString());\n});\ncmd.stderr.on('data', (err) => {\n  console.error(err.toString());\n});\n```\n\nbut the best I've been able to come up with for ethereum/go-ethereum/develop is this broken code, which for some reason won't obey the pipe and log to the file.\n\n``` javascript\nlet cmd = spawn('geth', ['--datadir=' + gethInstanceConfig.datadir,\n    '--port=' + gethInstanceConfig.port, '--rpc', '--rpcport=' +\n    gethInstanceConfig.rpcport, '--rpcaddr=' + gethInstanceConfig.rpcaddr, '--rpcapi=' +\n    gethInstanceConfig.rpcapi, '--networkid=' + gethInstanceConfig.networkid,\n    '--rpccorsdomain=' + gethInstanceConfig.rpccorsdomain, '--unlock=0',\n    '--password=' + gethInstanceConfig.password,\n    '--maxpeers=' + gethInstanceConfig.maxpeers, \n    'js ' + gethInstanceConfig.js, '| tee', '-a', gethInstanceConfig.logfile]);\n```\n\nthe strange thing is if I get the command being run from `ps aux | grep geth` and run it directly in the terminal everything works fine.\n",
