    "body": "I've found that simple output redirect doesn't work for some reason; but using `tee` like this does:\r\n\r\n``` sh\r\ngeth $OPTS 2>&1 | tee -a geth.log\r\n```\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nOtherwise, I'm usually running `geth` as a `systemd` service anyway, so capturing log is up to `journald`.",
